class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="falafel-inc" class="entry-website-title">Falafel Inc</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-falafel-inc-2024074-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-falafel-inc-2024074-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-falafel-inc-2024074-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Falafel Inc"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.falafelinc.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.falafelinc.org/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Washington, District of Columbia, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Falafel Inc is a food social enterprise based in Washington, D.C. The business serves falafels, hummus, and more, and in partnership with the World Food Programme, they help deliver aid to refugees. The website's single-page design covers the business's story, menu, press mentions, and reviews.</p><p>The straightforward design authentically conveys the business's commitment to simplicity. Visual elements stand out well with ample spacing against subtle background colors, and concise descriptions present key information in bite-sized portions.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site's anchor menu supports quick and easy navigation. Customer reviews and accolades featured in the news section build trust. High-quality imagery and concise, well-spaced content contribute to a pleasant user experience. The site performed well on WAVE, which flagged only a few contrast errors and one image missing alternative text.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The hero image is oversized, leading to a reduced impact. The business logo at the top of the website does not stand out well against the background. The body copy could stand to be bolder and larger for easier reading, particularly on the mobile site. The section about locations does not list any specific locations.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-falafel-inc-2024074-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-falafel-inc-2024074-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop site greets visitors with the unusual layout of a menu bar beneath the hero image, making it not instantly apparent. The anchor menu floats, making navigation on this one-page website even easier. Aside from the hero image, the visuals are well-sized and displayed with ample breathing room, showing them to their best advantage on the desktop version.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-falafel-inc-2024074-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-falafel-inc-2024074-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile site makes a more appealing first impression, thanks to the full length of the hero image displayed on the screen, even though it is cropped on both sides. It also features its menu in the more familiar position in the top-right corner of the page.</p><p>While the content is scaled down to fit a smaller screen, the body copy is rather small, making it less easy to read. The generous spacing on the desktop version is carried over to the mobile site but is less effective and would look better if the size of the graphics were reduced. On Google's PageSpeed Insights, the mobile site scored 56/100 for performance.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="equinox-design" class="entry-website-title">Equinox Design</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-equinox-design-2024074-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-equinox-design-2024074-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-equinox-design-2024074-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Equinox Design"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.equinox.design/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.equinox.design/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>India</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Equinox Design is a product and web design service provider based in India that caters to clients across the globe. The business's single-page website features a dark background that makes a bold, confident impression and against which its white text elements stand out well.</p><p>As users scroll down the page, they are introduced to the business's USPs, past projects, services offered, and pricing, with a helpful FAQs section toward the bottom of the page. It also features CTAs to engage visitors, along with graphics to highlight the business's points of differentiation.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site features multiple CTA buttons, encouraging user engagement. Some visuals are animated, giving the site a dynamic feel. With only two empty links and two low-contrast errors flagged, the site performed well on WAVE.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is missing an "About" section that introduces the business. The "Who's behind Equinox Design?" section seems more like an afterthought and would be more effective if it were incorporated into an "About" section toward the top of the page.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-equinox-design-2024074-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-equinox-design-2024074-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website's graphics really come to the fore on the desktop view, but the oversized headings have a somewhat overpowering effect. A floating anchor menu further simplifies navigation. While the desktop site scored an excellent 100/100 for both best practices and SEO on Google's PageSpeed Insights, it had a rather underwhelming performance score of 51/100.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-equinox-design-2024074-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-equinox-design-2024074-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>Similar to the desktop version, the mobile site features a floating menu. However, the gradient-changing colors of the backdrop in the top section are more noticeable. Unlike the desktop version, the images showcasing the business's work do not automatically rotate on the mobile site and users have to click through the images.</p><p>On Google's PageSpeed Insights test, the mobile site achieved the same top scores of 100/100 for best practices and SEO but had an even lower performance score of 28/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="beauty-with-intuition" class="entry-website-title">Beauty with Intuition</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
