class="container"><h2 id=fAQs class="section-heading">FAQs:</h2><div
class="row"><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-are-single-page-websites class="question">What are single-page websites?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Also referred to as one-page websites, single-page websites are sites that contain all their content on a single HTML page. These are typically laid out in a manner that allows visitors to scroll through the content vertically.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=when-should-i-consider-a-single-page-design class="question">When should I consider a single-page design?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Single-page websites are suitable for certain businesses and projects, such as simple, one-off projects, events, or new product launches. Startup businesses may also opt for a single-page website to begin with.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-create-a-one-page-website class="question">How do I create a one-page website?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>You can create a one-page website using a website builder.</p></div></div><div
